programme.title: Mastering Pressure Shooting For Hunting, Chasing November Update
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we head down to southern Iowa with the recently crowned ASA champion of both Missouri and Iowa to discuss a hot topic for this time of year. How to deal with pressure shooting and how you can practice that outside of a hunting situation. As deer hunters, we often find ourselves spending time trying to prepare each and every detail to have a successful season. E-scouting the maps, putting boots on the ground, hanging tree stands, adding food plots where applicable, and much more. However, one often overlooked part of that preparation is shooting your bow to help master shooting under pressure when an animal is in front of us. With this in mind, Owen Reigler and Josh Sparks sit down and discuss how with roughly 60 days to go until opening day in Iowa, folks can tackle this and see a big difference in confidence.

programme.title: Mike's Overlooked Secrets For Finding Big Bucks

With plenty of lessons learned over the years with the River Farm, Mike moves through the new property applying his 5 part process to break down a new spot for year one success. Through this process, Mike introduces multiple key spots, talks about how he identified them, and breaks down how he expects them to pay off this year. Finally, stick around until the very end of the video to see a first hand look at a great buck Mike filmed that he has history with.
